# PROJECTS.md — Developer Project Reference

How to discover project source location and navigate multi-project workspaces.

## Core rule

- `{{ host_projects_root_hint }}`/`{project_id}/...` is the project ticket area (kanban metadata and tasks), not necessarily the source repository location.
- The real project/source location must be read from `{{ host_projects_root_hint }}`/`{project_id}`/.project.location (single-line absolute path or canonical URI).
- Always read `.project.location` before touching any source code.

## Finding project source location

1. Infer `project_id` from the ticket filename (see TICKETS.md)
2. Read `{{ host_projects_root_hint }}`/`{project_id}`/.project.location
   - This file contains a single line: absolute path or canonical URI of the source repository
3. Navigate to that location for all code work

## Project metadata

- `{{ host_projects_root_hint }}`/`{project_id}`/project.md — shared knowledge from lead/team
  - Contains: project identity, tech stack, architecture notes, code standards, working knowledge
  - Read this before diving into implementation for context on conventions and constraints

## Pre-implementation check

Before writing any code:

1. Read `project.md` for the project context
2. Read `.project.location` to confirm the source path
3. Scan the repo structure at a high level (main entrypoints, key modules, test conventions)

## Worktree setup

- Always work in a per-ticket worktree (see TOOLS.md "Worktree conventions")
- Sync with main branch before starting work
- Name worktree by ticket id/slug, not by your name
